import { SITE_DESCRIPTION } from '@/lib/identity'
---
<BaseLayout
  title="gab44 — astrology with soul"
  description={SITE_DESCRIPTION}
  canonical="/"
  ogType="website"
  navCurrent="/"
  pageClass="page-home"
>
<div class="home-root">

    

    <div class="brand-mark"><span class="dot"></span> gab44 ✦ astrology with soul</div>
    <h1>readings, written for <span class="accent">one human</span> at a time.</h1>
    <p class="sub">
      Daily energy. Life-path mappings. Honest astrology
      behind every answer — built by someone who actually does this for his own family.
    </p>

    <div class="grid">
      <div class="card featured">
        <h2>✨ Daily horoscopes — all 12 signs</h2>
        <p>Today's energy for your sign — warm, modern, written daily. No "the planets align" filler. One concrete energy, one practical move, one tiny encouragement.</p>
        <a class="cta" href="/horoscopes">Read today's horoscope →</a>
        <div class="agent-row">
          <span class="pill pill-a"><span class="d"></span>updated daily</span>
          <span class="pill pill-b"><span class="d"></span>3-5 sentences</span>
          <span class="pill pill-c"><span class="d"></span>no woo-woo</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h2>💞 Zodiac compatibility — all 78 pairs</h2>
        <p>Every sign × every sign. The spark, the friction, the underrated gift, one move this week. Pick any two — yours and theirs.</p>
        <a class="cta outline" href="/compatibility">Browse pairs →</a>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h2>📜 Sign personalities — 12 deep profiles</h2>
        <p>Evergreen, careful guides to each zodiac sign — core energy, gifts, shadows, love, career, spiritual gift, the lesson of this lifetime.</p>
        <a class="cta outline" href="/horoscopes">Read the profiles →</a>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h2>🜂 Sign groups — elements &amp; modalities</h2>
        <p>The 4 elements (fire, earth, air, water) and 3 modalities (cardinal, fixed, mutable). Why your sign is the way it is — through the bigger pattern it belongs to.</p>
        <a class="cta outline" href="/elements">Browse the 7 patterns →</a>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h2>🌙 Moon signs — your inner weather</h2>
        <p>Your sun sign is who you act like. Your moon sign is how you actually feel — emotional core, attachment style, what soothes, what stresses. Twelve deep evergreen guides.</p>
        <a class="cta outline" href="/moon">Read your moon sign →</a>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h2>✨ Rising signs — the mask the world meets first</h2>
        <p>Your ascendant is the costume your soul wears in this lifetime — first impression, body style, social mask, defense mechanism, life chapters. The third leg of the big three.</p>
        <a class="cta outline" href="/rising">Read your rising sign →</a>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h2>🃏 Tarot — all 22 Major Arcana</h2>
        <p>From the Fool's leap to the World's completion. Twenty-two evergreen guides — upright meaning, reversed, in love, in career, the spiritual gift, the moment when you pull the card.</p>
        <a class="cta outline" href="/tarot">Read the cards →</a>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h2>🏛️ The 12 houses of astrology</h2>
        <p>Where the signs are <em>how</em> and the planets are <em>what</em>, the houses are <em>where</em>. Identity, money, home, partnership, transformation, career — twelve evergreen guides to the territory of your chart.</p>
        <a class="cta outline" href="/houses">Browse the houses →</a>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h2>🔢 Numerology — your life path number</h2>
        <p>Astrology reads the sky at your birth. Numerology reads the math. Nine single-digit paths plus three master numbers (11, 22, 33) — twelve evergreen guides to the number running underneath you.</p>
        <a class="cta outline" href="/numerology">Find your life path →</a>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h2>💎 Crystals & birthstones — three stones per sign</h2>
        <p>Not a curio cabinet — a working kit. An anchor stone, a companion, and one for the harder days. All twelve signs with traditional birthstones, how to use, what to avoid.</p>
        <a class="cta outline" href="/crystals">Find your stones →</a>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h2>✨ Angel numbers — 111, 222, 333, 11:11, more</h2>
        <p>When the same digits keep finding you, they're saying something. Thirteen evergreen guides — the spiritual message, in love, in career, twin flame, what to do when you see it.</p>
        <a class="cta outline" href="/angel-numbers">Read the numbers →</a>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h2>🪐 The 10 planets — how to read your birth chart</h2>
        <p>Sun, Moon, Mercury, Venus, Mars, Jupiter, Saturn, Uranus, Neptune, Pluto. The actors moving through your chart. A friendly map for reading the planets, return cycles included.</p>
        <a class="cta outline" href="/planets">Read the planets →</a>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h2>🟥🟧🟨💚🟦🟪 The 7 chakras — your energy map</h2>
        <p>Root, sacral, solar plexus, heart, throat, third eye, crown. What each centre governs, signs of an open vs blocked chakra, what blocks it, how to open it, four affirmations each. Pairs with crystals and healing sounds.</p>
        <a class="cta outline" href="/chakras">Walk the column →</a>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h2>↻ Major transits — Saturn return, Mercury retrograde &amp; more</h2>
        <p>The six big astrology moments — three retrogrades, two returns, the once-in-a-lifetime Pluto pass. What each one means, what it feels like, what to do, what to avoid, the deeper lesson. The seasons that mark a life.</p>
        <a class="cta outline" href="/transits">Read the transits →</a>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h2>△ ☌ □ The 7 aspects — how planets talk to each other</h2>
        <p>If signs are <em>how</em> and houses are <em>where</em>, aspects are <em>who they're talking to</em>. Conjunction, sextile, square, trine, opposition, quincunx, semi-sextile — the geometry of your inner conversation. Each with its gift, its work, and its lesson.</p>
        <a class="cta outline" href="/aspects">Read the aspects →</a>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h2>🌑🌓🌕🌗 The 8 phases of the moon — your monthly cycle</h2>
        <p>From the New Moon's blank page to the Full Moon's reveal to the Waning Crescent's quiet rest. Eight phases, each with its own ritual, its own work, its own lesson. Each guide pairs with a chakra, a healing meditation, and a stone.</p>
        <a class="cta outline" href="/lunar-phases">Walk the cycle →</a>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h2>🐉 The 12 animals of the Chinese zodiac</h2>
        <p>Rat, Ox, Tiger, Rabbit, Dragon, Snake, Horse, Goat, Monkey, Rooster, Dog, Pig — twelve year-animals carrying the five elements. Personality, in love, in career, who they match with, the year ahead. Pairs beautifully with your Western chart.</p>
        <a class="cta outline" href="/chinese-zodiac">Find your animal →</a>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h2>🐺 The 12 spirit animals walking with us</h2>
        <p>Wolf, Eagle, Bear, Owl, Lion, Hawk, Snake, Butterfly, Deer, Fox, Horse, Hummingbird — when an animal keeps showing up in your dreams or on your path, it's usually carrying a message. What each one means, when it appears, the gift, the shadow, the lesson. Each guide pairs with a chakra, a healing sound, and a stone.</p>
        <a class="cta outline" href="/spirit-animals">Meet your spirit animal →</a>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h2>💞 Twin flames — the 8 stages of the journey</h2>
        <p>Recognition, awakening, testing, crisis, runner &amp; chaser, surrender, reunion, mission. The most painful, most necessary spiritual relationship there is. What each stage feels like, how to know which one you're in, what helps, what to stop doing. Written warm, written by someone who has lived it.</p>
        <a class="cta outline" href="/twin-flames">Walk the journey →</a>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h2>💤 Dreams — what your unconscious is telling you</h2>
        <p>Snake, falling, teeth, being chased, water, death, flying, fire, naked, baby, spider, ex-partner. The 12 dreams every adult has had. What each is processing, the common variants, the warning, the gift, the question to ask yourself. Almost no dream is literal — and the unconscious works hard while you sleep.</p>
        <a class="cta outline" href="/dreams">Read your dream →</a>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h2>🃏 Tarot spreads — how to read each layout</h2>
        <p>Three-card, Celtic Cross, love, yes/no, career, daily draw, relationship, year-ahead. The 8 spreads every reader uses. When to pick each one, the position-by-position layout, how to read it, common mistakes, the deeper lesson. Pairs with the 22-card Major Arcana guides — each spread cross-links to the cards that show up most often inside it.</p>
        <a class="cta outline" href="/tarot/spreads">Pick a spread →</a>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h2>🌀 Personal Year cycle — what year of the 9-year cycle are you in?</h2>
        <p>Everyone is in a 9-year cycle. Year 1 plants seeds, Year 5 brings change, Year 7 is the inner year, Year 8 is harvest, Year 9 is closure. Calculate yours from your birth month + day + the current year. Each year carries its own theme, its own gift, its own shadow, its own daily practice. Knowing the year you are in is the difference between pushing against the current and using it. Distinct from your Life Path number (which is your soul's identity and does not change) — Personal Year is the energy of THIS calendar year for you specifically.</p>
        <a class="cta outline" href="/personal-year">Find your personal year →</a>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h2>🪬 The 8 clair senses — am I psychic? find your channel</h2>
        <p>Clairvoyance (clear seeing), clairaudience (clear hearing), claircognizance (clear knowing), clairsentience (clear feeling), clairempathy (clear emotional reading), clairalience (clear smelling), clairgustance (clear tasting), clairtangency (clear touching / psychometry). The 8 channels through which intuition speaks. Every human has at least one — most have a primary plus a secondary. Distinct from the 7 empath types (which is which kind of signal you receive); the clairs are <em>how the message gets in</em>.</p>
        <a class="cta outline" href="/clair-senses">Find your clair →</a>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h2>🎴 Tarot court cards — Page, Knight, Queen, King × 4 suits</h2>
        <p>The 16 court cards every reader gets stuck on — Page of Cups through King of Pentacles. Plus the 4 suit overviews (Cups=feeling, Wands=fire, Swords=mind, Pentacles=body). Read by rank for the maturity, by suit for the realm, then ask: who in my life is bringing this energy — or which version of me is being asked to step forward? Together with the 22 Majors and the 8 spreads, this completes the most-searched half of the 78-card tarot deck.</p>
        <a class="cta outline" href="/tarot/court">Read the court →</a>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h2>🃏 Tarot minor arcana — all 40 pip cards (Ace through Ten)</h2>
        <p>The 40 most-pulled cards in any tarot reading — Ace of Cups through Ten of Pentacles. Every card explained: upright meaning, reversed, in love, in work, the gift, the shadow, when you pull this card, three honest questions. Together with the 22 Majors, 16 Courts, 4 Suits, and 8 Spreads — this <strong>completes the full 78-card tarot deck</strong> on gab44. Read the suit for the realm (heart, will, mind, matter), the rank for the stage (1=beginning · 10=completion), then ask: where is this energy showing up in my life right now?</p>
        <a class="cta outline" href="/tarot/minors">Read all 40 minors →</a>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h2>🌈 Aura colors — the energy field around you</h2>
        <p>Red, orange, yellow, green, blue, indigo, violet, pink, white. The 9 main aura colors — what each one says about you, the gifts, the shadows, signs your aura is strong vs muddy. Distinct from chakras (which are inside the body); auras are the field around it.</p>
        <a class="cta outline" href="/auras">Read your aura →</a>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h2>✨ Manifestation methods — 369, scripting, pillow, whisper, mirror &amp; more</h2>
        <p>The 10 most popular methods explained without TikTok hype: 369, scripting, pillow, whisper, 5x55, two cup, 17-second rule, vision board, letter to the universe, mirror. How each one actually works, step-by-step, common mistakes, and the deeper truth most teachers leave out — including which one is right for which kind of desire.</p>
        <a class="cta outline" href="/manifestation">Pick your method →</a>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h2>💎 Crystals by intent — for anxiety, love, money, sleep, protection &amp; more</h2>
        <p>10 hand-written kits by what you're actually trying to feel or shift: crystals for anxiety, sleep, love, money, protection, confidence, grief, clarity, healing, manifestation. Top 3 stones per kit, supporting stones, how to use them, cleanse them, charge them — and the deeper truth about what crystals can and can't do. Distinct from per-sign crystals (which are about your zodiac); these are about your season.</p>
        <a class="cta outline" href="/crystals-intent">Pick your kit →</a>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h2>ᚠ Elder Futhark runes — all 24 meanings</h2>
        <p>Pulled a rune and want the meaning right now? All 24 Elder Futhark runes — Fehu (cattle, abundance) through Othala (ancestral home). Each one carries the upright reading, the reversed/merkstave reading, what it means in love and in work, the gift it teaches, and the shadow it casts. Norse divination, written warm — distinct from tarot (78 cards, narrative) because runes are 24 *forces*, closer to weather than to characters.</p>
        <a class="cta outline" href="/runes">Pull a rune →</a>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h2>☥ Spiritual symbols — 12 most-asked meanings</h2>
        <p>Wearing an ankh, a hamsa, an evil eye? Drawn to the lotus, the om, the triquetra in a dream? The 12 most-searched spiritual symbols across all of search — origin, meaning, the message it carries, the misuse to avoid, the gift it teaches, the shadow it casts. Four families: protection (hamsa, eye of horus, evil eye), devotion (ankh, om, lotus), cosmos (mandala, yin-yang, tree of life), pagan craft (triquetra, pentagram, triple moon). A symbol is not jewellery — it is a contract. Pick the one whose work you want to do.</p>
        <a class="cta outline" href="/symbols">Read a symbol →</a>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h2>💗 The 7 types of empath — which one are you?</h2>
        <p>You feel things other people don't feel. The question is *which* things, and *how* the information arrives. Three registers, seven types: feeling-types (emotional, physical), knowing-types (intuitive, heyoka), world-types (geomantic, plant-animal, dream). Every page has the actual signs (so you can recognise yourself), the gift you carry, the shadow it casts when untrained, and the protection practice that keeps the channel without making you the channel. Most empaths are a primary plus a secondary — read the closest type first.</p>
        <a class="cta outline" href="/empath-types">Find your type →</a>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h2>🌸 Sacred geometry — 10 patterns mystics keep pointing at</h2>
        <p>From the Flower of Life (the master pattern, found in Egyptian temples and Renaissance manuscripts) to the Fibonacci Spiral (nature's growth signature, in shells and galaxies). Three families: circles-of-life (flower, seed, fruit, vesica) = the unfolding family; cosmic 3D (metatron's cube, merkaba, platonic solids, torus) = the building blocks; flow patterns (sri yantra, fibonacci) = the growth signatures. Symbols hang on walls; geometries hold the wall up — meaning, history, and the practice each shape is asking you to embody.</p>
        <a class="cta outline" href="/sacred-geometry">Read a geometry →</a>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h2>🎧 Solfeggio frequencies — all 9 tones, what each one carries</h2>
        <p>From 174 Hz (foundation, the body settles) to 963 Hz (unity, separation dissolves). Six of the nine tones map one-to-one onto the chakras — the cleanest sound-to-body map there is. Each frequency has a job (release, change, love, connection, expression, awakening), a chakra, and a practice that makes it land. Honest about both what the tone *does* (signals permission) and what it *doesn't* (do the work for you).</p>
        <a class="cta outline" href="/solfeggio">Find your frequency →</a>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h2>🪷 The Eight Limbs of Yoga — Patanjali's path</h2>
        <p>The canonical 8-limb framework from the <em>Yoga Sutra</em> (c. 200 BCE-200 CE): <em>yama</em> (ethics) → <em>niyama</em> (observance) → <em>asana</em> (posture) → <em>pranayama</em> (breath) → <em>pratyahara</em> (sense-withdrawal) → <em>dharana</em> (concentration) → <em>dhyana</em> (meditation) → <em>samadhi</em> (absorption). The master frame that holds every body-practice and meditation-practice gab44 publishes — each limb page positions our mantras, mudras, asanas, and pranayamas as steps on this canonical path.</p>
        <a class="cta outline" href="/gab44/limbs">Walk the eight-limb path →</a>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h2>📿 Mantras — 12 sacred chants, what they mean &amp; how to chant</h2>
        <p>From <em>Om</em> (the seed of all sound) to <em>Om Ah Hum</em> (body, speech, mind). Three families: seed mantras (Om, So Hum, Sat Nam — the bija sounds), heart mantras (Om Mani Padme Hum, Lokah Samastah, Tara, Shanti — the compassion family), and power mantras (Gayatri, Om Namah Shivaya, Ganesha, Hare Krishna, Om Ah Hum — the devotion family). Each page has the actual lineage, the translation, the concrete chant practice, and honest framing about appropriation. Cross-tied to the chakra and the healing audio that pair with each one.</p>
        <a class="cta outline" href="/mantras">Read a mantra →</a>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h2>🤲 Mudras — 16 sacred hand gestures, what they carry &amp; how to hold</h2>
        <p>Sound + gesture is the canonical yogic-buddhist pairing — mudras are the body half of the offering mantras give voice to. From <em>Gyan</em> (the meditation gesture, finger meets thumb) and <em>Anjali</em> (palms at heart, namaste) to <em>Kalesvara</em> (the time-stilling gesture for the racing mind). Three families: foundation (Gyan, Chin, Anjali, Dhyana, Prana — the daily-gesture family), heart (Hridaya, Padma, Abhaya, Varada, Bhumisparsha — the compassion family), and power (Shuni, Surya, Vayu, Apana, Shunya, Kalesvara — the elemental family balancing the five elements and the inner planets). Each page has the lineage (Hatha Yoga Pradipika, Gheranda Samhita, Buddhist iconography), what the gesture does in the body and nervous system, how to form it (finger placement, breath, duration), the gift, the shadow.</p>
        <a class="cta outline" href="/gab44/mudras">Find your mudra →</a>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h2>🌬️ Pranayama — 10 breath practices, what they do &amp; how to practise</h2>
        <p>Breath is the third leg of the body-practice tripod. From <em>Nadi Shodhana</em> (the daily balancing breath, alternate-nostril) and <em>Ujjayi</em> (the ocean breath that holds a yoga practice together) to <em>Wim Hof</em> (the modern cold-and-breath protocol). Three families: foundation (Nadi Shodhana, Ujjayi, Diaphragmatic, Box — the daily-safe family), cooling (Bhramari humming-bee, Sitali tongue-curl, 4-7-8 — the parasympathetic family), and heating (Kapalabhati skull-shining, Bhastrika bellows, Wim Hof — the sympathetic family). Each page has the actual rhythm, the lineage, what the breath does in the body and the nervous system, and the contraindications named explicitly.</p>
        <a class="cta outline" href="/gab44/pranayama">Find your breath →</a>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h2>🧘 Asanas — 16 yoga poses, what they carry &amp; how to practise</h2>
        <p>Posture is the fourth leg of the body-practice quadrant — sound, gesture, breath, and now <em>shape</em>. From <em>Tadasana</em> (the daily standing pose, mountain) and <em>Balasana</em> (child's pose, the universal rest) to <em>Ananda Balasana</em> (the bliss-child pose). Four families: grounding (Mountain, Child, Down-Dog, Corpse — the daily family), heart (Cobra, Camel, Bridge, Fish — the chest-throat openers), power (Warrior One, Tree, Chair, Plank — the activating family), and restorative (Legs-Up-the-Wall, Butterfly, Seated Forward Fold, Happy Baby — the surrender family). Each page has the actual alignment, the Sanskrit lineage, the contraindications, the gift, and the shadow.</p>
        <a class="cta outline" href="/gab44/asanas">Find your pose →</a>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h2>👼 Archangels — meanings, signs &amp; how to call</h2>
        <p>The 9 most-invoked archangels — Michael (the sword that cuts every cord), Gabriel (the messenger of every great beginning), Raphael (the emerald healer of body and journey), Uriel (the lamp through the dark night), Chamuel (the rose-pink eye that finds what was lost), Jophiel (the sunflower that lifts the heavy thought), Zadkiel (the violet flame of forgiveness), Raziel (the keeper of mysteries), Metatron (the scribe at the throne, the soul-records). Each page has the actual lineage, 5 specific signs they are with you, the concrete invocation, the gift, and honest naming of the shadow.</p>
        <a class="cta outline" href="/archangels">Meet the archangels →</a>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h2>🌱 Doshas — find your Ayurvedic constitution</h2>
        <p>The medical-philosophical frame that the entire yogic body-practice quadrant sits inside. Three doshas — <em>vata</em> (air + ether, the moving), <em>pitta</em> (fire + water, the transforming), <em>kapha</em> (water + earth, the stabilizing). From the Charaka Samhita (c. 100 CE) and Sushruta Samhita (c. 600 BCE). Each page has the physical signs, the mental signs, the gift, the shadow, and how to balance with diet, asana, and pranayama. Pairs natively with the body-practice cluster — your dosha tells you which pranayama, which asana, which mantra is medicine for you specifically.</p>
        <a class="cta outline" href="/gab44/doshas">Find your dosha →</a>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h2>🌸 Bach Flower Remedies — all 38 essences</h2>
        <p>Dr. Edward Bach's 1936 system. The most emotionally direct surface in the funnel — each remedy addresses ONE specific named state. <strong>Fear (5):</strong> Rock Rose (terror), Mimulus (known fears), Cherry Plum (fear of losing control), Aspen (vague dread), Red Chestnut (fear for others). <strong>Uncertainty (6):</strong> Cerato, Scleranthus, Gentian, Gorse, Hornbeam, Wild Oat. <strong>Not present (7):</strong> Clematis (drift), Honeysuckle (past), Wild Rose (apathy), Olive (exhaustion), White Chestnut (loops), Mustard (cloud), Chestnut Bud (repeats). <strong>Loneliness (3):</strong> Water Violet, Impatiens, Heather. <strong>Over-sensitive (4):</strong> Agrimony (mask), Centaury (no boundaries), Walnut (transition), Holly (hatred). <strong>Despair (8):</strong> Larch, Pine, Elm, Sweet Chestnut, Star of Bethlehem, Willow, Oak, Crab Apple. <strong>Over-care (5):</strong> Chicory, Vervain, Vine, Beech, Rock Water. Each page: the state, the shift, in love, in work, a 5-minute practice, chakra + crystal pair.</p>
        <a class="cta outline" href="/gab44/bach-flowers">Find your remedy →</a>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h2>🌙 Nakshatras — all 27 Vedic lunar mansions</h2>
        <p>The finer-resolution Vedic wheel — the 27 divisions of the ecliptic the Moon traverses in a sidereal month, three nakshatras to every two zodiac signs. <em>Ashwini</em> (the first hooves, Aries 0°), <em>Bharani</em> (the bearing-vessel, Yama's threshold), <em>Krittika</em> (Agni's purifying blade, the foster-mothers of Skanda), <em>Rohini</em> (the Moon's exaltation, the chariot of growth) … through to <em>Revati</em> (Pushan's safe passage, the fish that brings the wanderer home, Pisces 30°). Lineage: Vedanga Jyotisha (c. 1400-1200 BCE), Brihat Parashara Hora Shastra (c. 4th c. CE). Each page has the deity, the planetary ruler, the symbol, the gana, what the nakshatra is in love and in work, the gift, the shadow. Your <em>Moon's nakshatra</em> is the single most predictive Vedic placement — finer than a Sun-sign, more specific than a Vedic dosha.</p>
        <a class="cta outline" href="/gab44/nakshatras">Find your nakshatra →</a>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h2>🌿 Yamas &amp; Niyamas — the 10 ethics of Patanjali</h2>
        <p>The first two limbs of yoga, expanded into the 10 individual ethics they contain. <strong>5 yamas (outward, sunrise saffron):</strong> <em>ahimsa</em> (non-violence), <em>satya</em> (truthfulness), <em>asteya</em> (non-stealing), <em>brahmacharya</em> (right use of energy), <em>aparigraha</em> (non-grasping). <strong>5 niyamas (inward, dusk indigo):</strong> <em>saucha</em> (cleanliness), <em>santosha</em> (contentment), <em>tapas</em> (discipline), <em>svadhyaya</em> (self-study), <em>ishvara-pranidhana</em> (surrender to the divine). From Yoga Sutras 2.30 + 2.32. Each page names the sutra reference, the <em>fruit</em> Patanjali names (YS 2.35–2.45 — "in the presence of one rooted in ahimsa, hostility ceases" / "from contentment, unsurpassable happiness" / "from surrender, samadhi itself"), and a 30-day practice. The ground under every other practice.</p>
        <a class="cta outline" href="/gab44/yamas-niyamas">Walk the 10 ethics →</a>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h2>🌳 Sefirot — Tree of Life, all 10 sephirot</h2>
        <p>The Kabbalistic <em>Etz Chaim</em> — the canonical Western mystical map. Ten sephirot down three pillars: <em>Kether</em> (crown, the unknowable source), <em>Chokmah</em> &amp; <em>Binah</em> (wisdom and understanding), <em>Chesed</em> &amp; <em>Geburah</em> (mercy and severity), <em>Tiferet</em> (beauty, the heart of the tree), <em>Netzach</em> &amp; <em>Hod</em> (eternity and splendor), <em>Yesod</em> (foundation, dream and astral), <em>Malkuth</em> (kingdom, embodied earth). Lineage: Sefer Yetzirah (c. 200 CE), the Zohar (c. 1280 CE), Lurianic Kabbalah (c. 1570 CE). Each sefirah page pairs with its archangel, planet, tarot card, and chakra — the densest internal-link surface on gab44.</p>
