        <h2>☯ I Ching — all 64 hexagrams</h2>
        <p>The <em>Yi Jing</em>, the <em>Book of Changes</em> — c. 1000 BCE Zhou-dynasty core, the oldest divination text in continuous use. Sixty-four hand-written guides in classical King Wen order. The Creative · The Receptive · Difficulty at the Beginning · Waiting · Conflict · The Army · ... · Before Completion. Four families: Beginnings (the foundational images), Cycles (how the situation moves), Trials (the descent and the well), Completion (revolution, cauldron, before-and-after). Each page: the hexagram, when you pull it, the changing lines, in love, in work, the gift, the shadow.</p>
