      <div class="card">
        <h2>🪷 Hindu Devas — the 12 most-searched Sanskrit deities</h2>
        <p>The <em>who</em> behind every mantra, mudra, asana, pranayama, eight-limb, yama/niyama, klesha, dosha, and nakshatra already on gab44. Four families. <strong>Trimurti</strong> (saffron / sky-blue / obsidian): <em>Brahma</em> the creator, <em>Vishnu</em> the preserver, <em>Shiva</em> the transformer. <strong>Avatars</strong> (indigo / jade / sindoor): <em>Krishna</em> the divine lover, <em>Rama</em> the dharmic king, <em>Hanuman</em> the perfect devotee. <strong>Mahadevis</strong> (gold / white / crimson / rose): <em>Lakshmi</em> abundance, <em>Saraswati</em> wisdom, <em>Durga</em> warrior, <em>Parvati</em> devoted householder. <strong>Sons of Shiva</strong> (rose / peacock): <em>Ganesh</em> remover of obstacles, <em>Kartikeya</em> spiritual warrior. Each page: source-text (Rig Veda hymn / Purana / Ramayana / Gita / Kalidasa / Tulsidas / Arunagirinathar), the iconography, the canonical invocation, in love + in work, the gift, the shadow (Hindutva weaponization, commercial flattening, appropriation — named honestly per deva), paired chakra + mantra.</p>
