      <div class="card">
        <h2>☥ Egyptian Gods — 12 deities of the Two Lands</h2>
        <p>The densest grief / death / threshold / household-protection cluster in all of comparative mythology. Three families. <strong>Solar Court</strong> (gold / coral / amber / crimson): <em>Ra</em> the king who fights Apophis at the seventh hour, <em>Horus</em> the falcon-heir who inherits the throne, <em>Hathor</em> the golden cow-mother of joy and music, <em>Sekhmet</em> the lioness whose Festival of Drunkenness brings her home. <strong>Osirian Cycle</strong> (green / lapis / black / red): <em>Osiris</em> the first who died and rose, <em>Isis</em> Great-of-Magic who gathered the fourteen pieces, <em>Anubis</em> the jackal at the Weighing of the Heart, <em>Set</em> the brother-disturber who also slays Apophis nightly. <strong>Memphite &amp; Hermopolitan</strong> (turquoise / mercury / feather-white / cat-green): <em>Ptah</em> the master-craftsman who creates by heart-and-tongue (the Logos-theology fifteen centuries before John's Gospel), <em>Thoth</em> Trismegistus scribe-of-the-gods, <em>Ma'at</em> the cosmic-truth-feather, <em>Bastet</em> the household-cat-protector. Each page: Pyramid-Text / Coffin-Text / Book-of-the-Dead / Plutarch / Herodotus source-honest, iconography, invocation, in love + in work, the gift, the shadow (Egyptomania racial-erasure, Hollywood-Anubis-as-villain, Thelemic Horus, New-Age Isis, white-nationalist Set, the silent extraction of Ptah-Logos and Ma'at-wisdom into Hermetic / Christian / New-Age Western religion — named honestly per god), paired zodiac sign + planet.</p>
