      <div class="card">
        <h2>🥁 Orishas — the 12 deities of the Yoruba pantheon</h2>
        <p>The first Afro-diasporic pantheon on gab44. The orishas of the Yoruba homeland (southwestern Nigeria) and the African Atlantic diaspora — Cuban Lukumí / Santería, Brazilian Candomblé, the African-American spiritual lineages — whose festivals on the beaches of Salvador da Bahia and Rio de Janeiro every December 31 and February 2 fill the Atlantic with white-clad celebrants by the million. Three families. <strong>Heads of Heaven</strong> (white-cloth / red-and-black / volcano / deep-indigo): <em>Obatalá</em> the cool-headed elder who sculpted human heads from clay and owns every <em>orí</em> (destiny-of-the-head), <em>Eleguá</em> (Èṣù-Elégbára) the crossroads-opener honored-first in every ritual and catastrophically mistranslated by 19th-c. missionaries as "the devil," <em>Aganjú</em> the volcano-king-and-ferryman of the impossible-passage (syncretized as Saint Christopher), <em>Olokun</em> the unseen owner of the depths whose face you cannot look at and who in diaspora-practice became the ancestor of the Middle-Passage drowned. <strong>Mothers & Lovers of Water</strong> (ocean-blue / river-gold / storm-purple / earth-burlap): <em>Yemayá</em> (Iemanjá) the mother of all orishas whose Brazilian December-31-beach-festival is the largest Afro-religious gathering in the world, <em>Oshún</em> the river-of-honey-and-gold patron-saint of Cuba and the only female orisha who can speak Ifá, <em>Oyá</em> (Iansã) the storm-wind-and-cemetery-gatekeeper who is the only orisha who can lead the dead through the gates, <em>Babalú-Ayé</em> the wounded-healer-of-disease syncretized as Saint Lazarus the leper who in the 1980s-90s diaspora became the primary orisha of refuge for HIV-positive practitioners. <strong>Warriors & Hunters of the Forest</strong> (thunder-red-white / iron-green-black / bow-turquoise / herb-green): <em>Shangó</em> the king of thunder who was the historical fourth Alaafin of the Oyo Empire (<em>Oba ko so</em> — the king did not hang), <em>Ogún</em> the owner of iron and road-cutter whose modern domain has expanded to cars-airplanes-electronics, <em>Oshosi</em> the hunter-archer of justice whose Saint-Sebastian syncretization is the namesake of Rio de Janeiro, <em>Òsanyìn</em> the one-eyed-one-armed-one-legged owner of all herbs without whose permission no other orisha can be fed. Each page: Ifá-Odu / Pataki / Bascom / Verger / Cabrera / Thompson source-honest, iconography, invocation, in love + in work, the gift, the shadow (Eshu-as-devil missionary mistranslation, Hollywood voodoo demonization, Catholic-saint syncretization as both survival-strategy and modern-erasure, post-2015 uninitiated-white commercial commodification — named honestly per orisha), lineage-respectful (introduction-not-consecration), paired zodiac sign + planet + chakra.</p>
