      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h2>𒀭 Mesopotamian Gods — the 12 Sumerian-Akkadian-Babylonian deities · the cradle of the zodiac</h2>
        <p>The seventh great pantheon on gab44 — and the <em>oldest written religion</em> on the site (clay-tablet attestation from c. 3000 BCE Sumer) and the <em>literal source</em> of the 12-sign zodiac and the 7 classical planets that every other astrological surface on gab44 is downstream of (the MUL.APIN astronomical compendium c. 1000 BCE is the canonical source-document). Three families. <strong>Anu-Enlil sovereigns of the cosmos</strong> (sky-blue / wind-storm / fresh-water / primordial-salt): <em>Anu</em> sky-father atop the 7-tier ziggurat-cosmos, <em>Enlil</em> wind-and-storm Lord-of-the-Air whose Ekur temple at Nippur was the cosmic-centre, <em>Enki / Ea</em> the freshwater-craftsman-trickster of the Abzu who saved humanity in Atra-Hasis (the Mesopotamian Noah), <em>Tiamat</em> the primordial salt-water-mother defeated by Marduk in the Enuma Elish. <strong>Astral court</strong> (sun-gold / moon-silver / Venus-rose / city-purple): <em>Shamash / Utu</em> sun-judge under whose patronage Hammurabi received the Code, <em>Sin / Nanna</em> moon-king whose Lament for Ur is the oldest preserved city-elegy, <em>Inanna / Ishtar</em> the Descent-to-the-Underworld goddess whose three-days-on-the-hook predates Christ by 2,000 years, <em>Marduk</em> Babylon's patron who killed Tiamat and built the cosmos from her body. <strong>Underworld &amp; specialists</strong> (war-red / scribe-indigo / hunter-bronze / queen-obsidian): <em>Nergal</em> plague-and-war king of Kutha, <em>Nabu</em> the scribal Lord of Ezida at Borsippa whose name became the Hebrew nāḇîʾ "prophet" (Mount Nebo), <em>Ninurta</em> hunter-warrior of the Anzu-Bird-slaying epic, <em>Ereshkigal</em> queen of the underworld and Inanna's elder sister. Enuma-Elish, Gilgamesh, Descent-of-Inanna, Atra-Hasis, Hammurabi, Enheduanna, MUL.APIN source-honest. Biblical-extraction-honest: Atra-Hasis→Noah, Hammurabi→Mosaic law, Nabu→nāḇîʾ, Inanna→Marian Queen-of-Heaven, three-days-on-the-hook→resurrection. First pantheon on gab44 covering ALL 12 zodiac signs.</p>
        <a class="cta outline" href="/gab44/mesopotamian-gods">Meet the 12 Mesopotamian gods →</a>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h2>🪶 Aztec / Mexica Gods — the 12 deities of Tenochtitlán</h2>
        <p>The eighth great pantheon — and the <em>first pre-Columbian pantheon</em> on gab44, closing the geographic gap of the Americas. The youngest fully-documented great pantheon (Tenochtitlán 1325-1521 CE, less than 200 years of imperial-cult-practice but inheriting a millennium of pre-Mexica Mesoamerican religion from the Olmecs c. 1200 BCE, Teotihuacan c. 100-650 CE, and the Toltecs c. 950-1150 CE) — and the only one with <em>first-generation conquistador-and-friar ethnography</em> (Bernardino de Sahagún interviewed surviving Mexica elders in Nahuatl in the 1550s-1580s and the 12-book Florentine Codex is the result). Three families. <strong>Primordial &amp; Cosmic</strong> (cosmic-violet / quetzal-jade / smoking-obsidian / Fifth-Sun-coral): <em>Ometeotl</em> the cosmic-dual-principle of Omeyocan-the-thirteenth-heaven invoked only in the philosophical-poetry of the tlamatinime; <em>Quetzalcoatl</em> the feathered-serpent civilizer-priest-king whose return-prophecy Moctezuma II mistook for Cortés in 1519 — the single-most-politically-consequential religious-mistake in world history; <em>Tezcatlipoca</em> the smoking-mirror trickster-fate-god whose Toxcatl-festival was the site of Pedro de Alvarado's 1520 massacre; <em>Tonatiuh</em> the Fifth-Sun whose Calendar Stone is the single-most-iconic Mexica sculpture. <strong>Earth, Water &amp; Fertility</strong> (storm-jaguar-blue / jade-river-teal / serpent-skirt-forest / cherry-cosmic-pink): <em>Tlaloc</em> the goggle-eyed storm-god with iconography unchanged from Teotihuacan c. 100 CE through 1521; <em>Chalchiuhtlicue</em> the jade-skirted lady-of-all-surface-water whose baptism-rite became Catholic baptism in unbroken continuity; <em>Coatlicue</em> the serpent-skirted earth-mother whose Coatlicue-Monolith was twice-buried by 18th-c. antiquarians as too-frightening; <em>Xochiquetzal</em> the flower-quetzal goddess of beauty, art, the in-xochitl-in-cuicatl flower-and-song aesthetic. <strong>War, Death &amp; Renewal</strong> (Mexica-blue / Mictlan-violet / Xipe-crimson / cosmic-Milky-Way): <em>Huitzilopochtli</em> the Hummingbird-of-the-Left whose eagle-on-the-cactus-with-the-snake omen is still the Mexican flag five centuries after conquest; <em>Mictlantecuhtli</em> the skeletal king of Mictlan whose Hueymiccailhuitl is the direct ancestor of the modern Day-of-the-Dead; <em>Xipe Totec</em> the Flayed Lord of agricultural-spring-renewal whose maize-seed-cosmology-applied-to-the-human-warrior-body is the most-philosophically-difficult Mexica ritual; <em>Mixcoatl</em> the Cloud-Serpent of the Milky-Way and cosmic-father of the Chichimec-hunter-lineage. Florentine-Codex / Codex-Borgia / Leyenda-de-los-Soles / Cantares-Mexicanos source-honest. Shadow-honest about Cortés 1519-1521, Landa's auto-da-fé 1562, the Black Legend, the Mexicayotl revival, the Penacho de Moctezuma repatriation dispute, and the 2017-2020 tzompantli skull-rack archaeological reinterpretations.</p>
        <a class="cta outline" href="/gab44/aztec-gods">Meet the 12 Aztec gods →</a>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h2>⛩ Shinto Kami — the 12 deities of the Japanese pantheon</h2>
        <p>The ninth great pantheon — and the <em>first East Asian pantheon</em> on gab44, closing the geographic gap of East Asia. Uniquely among great-world-pantheons, the only one that is still the <em>state-recognized national-cultic system of a contemporary G7 country</em> (~80,000 active Shinto shrines across Japan, ~3% identify as Shintoist but ~70% participate in at least one annual Shinto ritual). Three families. <strong>Celestial / Amatsukami</strong> (sun-gold / storm-cobalt / moon-silver / dawn-rose): <em>Amaterasu</em> the sun-goddess and ancestress of the imperial-line whose Ise Naikū has been rebuilt every 20 years for 1,300 years in the Shikinen Sengū continuity; <em>Susanoo</em> the storm-and-sea brother whose Yamata-no-Orochi slaying at the Hi River in Izumo produced the Kusanagi sword; <em>Tsukuyomi</em> the silent mysterious moon-brother whose Ukemochi-slaying ended cosmic sun-moon co-presence; <em>Ame-no-Uzume</em> the dawn-dancer whose ecstatic dance on the overturned tub at the heavenly-river-bed lured Amaterasu out of the Iwato rock-cave — the foundational performing-arts narrative of every kagura, gigaku, bugaku, noh, kabuki, and butoh. <strong>Earthly / Kunitsukami</strong> (earth-brown / vermillion-fox / forest-stag / dragon-blue): <em>Ōkuninushi</em> great-land-master of Izumo and kami of enmusubi-binding-of-all-relationships, host of the annual October Kamiari-conference at Izumo Taisha; <em>Inari</em> rice-and-fox-kami of ~32,000 of Japan's ~80,000 shrines (the most-numerous single kami), patron of Fushimi Inari Taisha with its iconic 10,000+ vermillion torii; <em>Sarutahiko</em> the great earthly-kami who met Ninigi at the Eight-Crossroads-of-Heaven and was disarmed by Uzume's laughing-grin; <em>Watatsumi</em> the dragon-king of the underwater Ryūgū-jō Dragon-Palace, source of the two cosmic-tide-jewels and cosmic-maternal-grandfather of the imperial-line via Toyotama-hime. <strong>Syncretic / Shinbutsu</strong> (warrior-purple / Sarasvatī-pearl / fisherman-coral / cherry-blossom-pink): <em>Hachiman</em> the warrior-Bodhisattva of ~25,000 shrines, the first kami granted the Buddhist title Daibosatsu in 749 CE inaugurating the honji-suijaku synthesis, patron of the Minamoto samurai and the Kamakura shogunate; <em>Benzaiten</em> the Indian-Vedic Sarasvatī arrived via the Sutra of Golden Light and fully-Japanized as the only female of the Seven Lucky Gods; <em>Ebisu</em> the only-fully-Japanese member of the Seven Lucky Gods, originally the rejected leech-child Hiruko cast out to sea and cosmic-rehabilitated as the laughing-fisherman-luck-kami; <em>Konohana-no-Sakuya-hime</em> the cherry-blossom-and-Mount-Fuji princess and cosmic-foundational figure of <em>mono no aware</em> (the cosmic-aesthetic of the pathos of ephemeral things). Kojiki (712 CE) / Nihon Shoki (720 CE) / Engishiki (927 CE) / Fudoki / Norito / Manyōshū / Motoori-Norinaga / Hardacre source-honest. Shadow-honest about the 1868 Meiji Shinbutsu-bunri separation that destroyed the 1,200-year-old Buddhist-Shinto honji-suijaku synthesis, State Shinto 1868-1945, the imperial-divinity-myth and Yasukuni-controversy, the Lafcadio-Hearn / Joseph-Campbell Western reductions to "nature-religion," and the post-Studio-Ghibli kami-as-anime-spirits flattening.</p>
