      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h2>🐦‍⬛ Norse Gods — the 10 beings behind the runes</h2>
        <p>The peer pantheon to the Hindu devas. The Eddic gods the Elder Futhark on gab44 has been invoking silently in every cast — and the Norse strand behind Yule on the Wheel of the Year. Three families. <strong>Aesir court</strong> (Asgard sky): <em>Odin</em> the Allfather (one-eyed, hanged on Yggdrasil for the runes), <em>Thor</em> the thunderer, <em>Loki</em> the trickster, <em>Frigg</em> the foreknowing queen, <em>Tyr</em> the one-handed lawspeaker, <em>Heimdall</em> the watcher at Bifrost, <em>Baldur</em> the shining-one-who-returns-after-Ragnarök. <strong>Vanir</strong> (earth-fertility, taught seidr to the Aesir): <em>Freya</em> the lady of seidr, <em>Freyr</em> the sacred king who gave away his sword for love. <strong>Helheim</strong>: <em>Hel</em>, daughter of Loki, queen of the ordinary dead — the figure most distorted by Christianization. Each page: Eddic source (Poetic Edda, Snorri 1220, Saxo 1200, Adam of Bremen 1075, Tacitus 98), iconography, invocation, in love + in work, the gift, the shadow (folkish/SS appropriation, Marvel-flattening, Christianization — named honestly per god), paired rune + sabbat.</p>
        <a class="cta outline" href="/gab44/norse-gods">Meet the 10 Norse gods →</a>
      </div>

